      "type": "explanation",
      "content": [
        { "type": "title", "value": "Possession: ge3" },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "The particle <strong>嘅</strong> (ge3) is used to indicate possession, similar to ''s' in English. Simply add it after a person or pronoun."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "我嘅",
          "romanization": "ngo5 ge3",
          "translation": "Mine / My"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "你嘅",
          "romanization": "nei5 ge3",
          "translation": "Yours / Your"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "佢嘅書",
          "romanization": "keoi5 ge3 syu1",
          "translation": "His/Her book"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "It can also be used at the end of a sentence to emphasize a characteristic or to mean 'the one that is...'"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "邊個嘅？",
          "romanization": "bin1 go3 ge3?",
          "translation": "Whose is it? (Which one's?)"
        }
      ]
    },
    { "type": "reading", "exerciseId": "3.6.2" },
    { "type": "unscramble", "exerciseId": "3.6.3" },
    {
      "type": "dialog",
      "lines": [
        {
          "speaker": "A",
          "cantonese": "呢個係唔係你嘅書呀？",
          "romanization": "ni1 go3 hai6 m4 hai6 nei5 ge3 syu1 aa3?",
          "translation": "Is this your book?"
        },
        {
          "speaker": "B",
          "cantonese": "唔係。係佢嘅。",
          "romanization": "m4 hai6. hai6 keoi5 ge3.",
          "translation": "No. It is his."
        },
        {
          "speaker": "A",
          "cantonese": "哦，好呀。",
          "romanization": "o4, hou2 aa3.",
          "translation": "Oh, okay."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
